All,

I've got the second version of the client script stable and bug-free enough 
that I *think* I'm ready for other people to run the client, too.  You can 
find it here:

http://www.hanlonsrazor.com:81/neat/iex/iex_client.tar.bz2

Note:  If your client machine is a Linux 2.6 machine, you can opt to 
download pre-compiled
(-march=i686 -O3), statically linked binaries.  In the config file, set 
MODE=bin.

The client runs perfectly under cygwin (http://sources.redhat.com/cygwin/), 
so windows users can contribute, too.  They just have to work from the 
sources.

I'll be building all the fancy reports and graphs this weekend.  This new 
version will have a lot more cool stuff I can show. :)  In the mean time, 
you can see what (little) has been created (or check on my progress) here:

http://www.hanlonsrazor.com:81/neat/iex/reports/

Thanks!

-- John
